articles.author: Gram Slattery, David Lawder
articles.description: Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump was safe on Sunday after the Secret Service foiled what the FBI called an apparent assassination attempt while he was golfing on his course in West Palm Beach, Florida.
articles.title: Trump safe after new assassination attempt thwarted at Florida golf course

articles.author: Brad Brooks, Alexandra Ulmer
articles.description: A gunman attempted to assassinate Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump on Sunday at Trump's golf course in Palm Beach, Florida, authorities said.
articles.title: Trump golf course shooting; What we know about the reported suspect

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Typhoon Bebinca made landfall in Shanghai on Monday morning as a Category 1 storm, the most powerful tropical cyclone to directly hit the Chinese financial hub in more than seven decades.
articles.title: Typhoon Bebinca lands in Shanghai, strongest storm to hit city since 1949

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Mexico's judicial reform overhauling the country's courts, which will allow voters to elect judges, officially took effect on Sunday after the text of the constitutional changes was published in the government gazette.
articles.title: Mexico's sweeping judicial overhaul formally takes effect

articles.author: David W Cerny, Marek Strzelecki
articles.description: One person drowned in southwest Poland and thousands were evacuated across the border in the Czech Republic after heavy rain continued to batter central Europe on Sunday, causing flooding in several parts of the region.
articles.title: Floods claim two more casualties as torrential rain batters central Europe

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia launched its eighth air attack in September on Kyiv overnight, with air defence units destroying nearly 20 drones that were heading towards the country's capital, Ukrainian military said on Monday.
articles.title: Russia launches drone attack on Kyiv, Ukraine's military says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A surface-to-surface missile fired at central Israel from Yemen hit an unpopulated area, causing no injuries, Israel's military said on Sunday.
articles.title: Missile fired from Yemen set off sirens in central Israel, military says

articles.author: Jose Devasia
articles.description: A 24-year-old student has died from the Nipah virus in the southern Indian state of Kerala, a local medical official said on Monday, and 151 people who came into contact with the victim are under observation to prevent the spread of the deadly virus.
articles.title: One dead from Nipah virus in India's Kerala; second death this year

articles.author: Douglas Gillison
articles.description: The FBI said on Sunday it was assessing the credibility of threats against Haitians at Wittenberg University following baseless claims by Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump that the migrants in the town were eating cats and dogs.
articles.title: FBI looking into anti-Haitian threats at Springfield, Ohio, university
